    "On average across both tests, the bare bones prompt approach provided the worst scores overall.",
    "On the quantitative test, bare bones performed comparably to the other prompt approaches, but on the verbal ability test-particularly with GPT-3.5-bare bones performed much worse than the other prompt approaches (average score of 7 compared to average score 12.92 or above for the other prompt approaches).",
    "Bare bones also performed worse than the other prompt approaches with GPT-4 on the verbal ability test, but the differences were much more minor.",
    "On average across both tests, the chain-of-thought prompt approach yielded the best scores.",
